0.task: Touch all objects that are small.

TEACHER.observations: I led by example. They then repeated and for every subsequent map, they applied the same logic of touching "all small objects".

2.task: Touch all objects that are blue.

STUDENT.observations: It was confusing because I had to guess what the other person was trying to show me
STUDENT.guess: Touch objects that are blue and red

TEACHER.observations: I taught the lesson three times and it was only on the third lesson that I realized I had to make the rule generalized. It's challenging when the teaching map doesnt include all situations that apply (ie just two blue small squares instead of big/small blue square and big/small blue triangle). Instead of "touch all blue objects" exclusively, I suggested the student touch all objects which happens to include all blue objects. I'm not certain why the last map was unsuccessful.
